A vulnerability, which was classified as <a href="https://vuldb.com/kb/risk">critical</a>, has been found in <a href="https://vuldb.com/product/jeecgboot">JeecgBoot up to 3.9.1</a>. Affected by this issue is some unknown functionality of the file <em>/sys/dict/loadTreeData</em> of the component <em>JSON Object Handler</em>. The manipulation of the argument <em>condition</em> leads to sql injection.

This vulnerability is documented as <a href="https://vuldb.com/cve/CVE-2026-8114">CVE-2026-8114</a>. The attack can be initiated remotely. Additionally, an exploit exists.

The vendor confirms (translated from Chinese): &quot;It should have been fixed; a batch of issues were recently resolved.&quot;
